There is definately two problems here.

1. asyncExec doesn't guarantee a synchronization point.  Jobs are added to the
"current" fRunnables.
2. AsynchJob.run() doesn't have a "stable" synchronization block.
			synchronized (fRunnables) {
				v = fRunnables;
				fRunnables = new Vector(5);
			}
While this works, you cannot use fRunnables as the synchronized object for #1. 
Therefore the above code must be changed.
